<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1912-08-20T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1912-08-20T00:00:00-05:00" n="1618" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d1618">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 819.77/129.</note>
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">American Minister</gloss> to
                                the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss></hi>.</head>
                        <opener>
                            <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.—Paraphrase.]</seg>
                        </opener>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">American Legation</hi>, <lb/>
                                    <hi rend="italic">Panama</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1912-08-20">
                                    <hi rend="italic">August 20, 1912</hi></date>.</dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>Department’s telegram of May 31. The Minister of Public Works is
                            apparently disposed to sign the contract, and the Minister for Foreign
                            Affairs assures me that if signed it will conform to all the conditions
                            of that telegram. He adds, however, that it would seem not proper for
                            the present administration to sign a contract of this nature, as it has
                            only five more weeks of tenure, especially as the President-elect,
                            Porras, recently informed me that he did not approve of constructing
                            this section of the Panamá-David railroad first.</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">Dodge.</hi>
                            </signed>
                        </closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>